generate_cpcconf.py:
	This python script generates output in the format of the cpcconf.ini file. Before you start
	make sure all drivers you need are loaded and all devices that should be recognized are
	pluged-in.
	
	Example call:
	python generate_cpcconf.py > cpcconf.ini

	This starts the script any save its output to a file called cpcconf.ini. To use this file
	for CPCLIB copy the file to /etc/cpcconf.ini (as root).

	CPC-XT:
	If you use an CPC-XT this script did not set the right IrqNr, this has to be done manually
	in the appropriate channel section in the cpcconf.ini file.
